title.narrative: 90% of OCs providing timely and accurate data through MIS.

comment.narrative: 4% of the data is either incomplete or not reported in a timely fashion, but still contributes useful information for programevaluation and planning.

title.narrative: Improved household expenditure rates or improved access to economic and social services in 80% kelurahans in 2011

comment.narrative: 90% of 8,795 kelurahans. Source: Final Report of Quantitative Evaluation the National Community Empowerment Program-Urban 2011.

title.narrative: Min.80% of local governments provide cost-sharing: 20% cost sharing for local governments with low fiscal capacity, and 50% cost-sharing for local governments with high fiscal capacity.

comment.narrative: 91% of LGs have provided required cost-sharing.

title.narrative: Min.70% of infrastructure works evaluated as of good quality.

comment.narrative: About 96% of the works are of good quality (source: spot check of NMC)

title.narrative: Infrastructure built is at least 20% cheaper than that built by non-community based approaches in 80% of participating kelurahans

comment.narrative: Achieved in 94% of 8,795 kelurahans. Source: NMC (National Management Consultant), based on spot-checking.

title.narrative: At least 80% satisfaction level of beneficiaries regarding improved services and local level governance

comment.narrative: Average of 85% Survey (Source: Final Report of Quantitative Evaluation the National Community Empowerment Program-Urban 2011) and87% Spot check held by NMC (National Management Consultant)

title.narrative: Number of each type of infrastructure, economic, and social activities completed in 80% participating kelurahans (wards).

target.value: Investments in 6,240 kelurahans, but type not specified.

comment.narrative: As a CDD project, there were no set of targets for specific types of the investments and activities.

Investments in 8,443 kelurahans so far, the kelurahan grants have financedover 8,460 km of small roads, 2,530 km of drainage andirrigation canals, reconstruction of 35,464 of the poorest houses, 36,232 units of solid waste and sanitation facilities, and 1,773community health facilities. It has also financed 43,300 economic activities through the RLFs.

title.narrative: Min.70% of kelurahans with revolving loan funds (RLFs) having a loans at risk (LAR) ratio greater than three months will be less than 10%.
Min.40% participation rate of poorest and vulnerable community members in planning and decision making meetings.
Min.30% participation rate of women as member or community groups (KSMs)
Min. 90% of kelurahans with RLFs have annualized return of investment of >10%
Minimum 40% participation rate of women in planning and decision making meetings
Min. 90% of kelurahans with RLFs have a cost coverage ratio of >125%
